<!--
  j2n6s300_standalone.xacro
  ─────────────────────────
  Standalone xacro for Kinova Jaco v2 6DOF non-spherical 3-finger (j2n6s300).

  Modeled after j2n7s300_standalone.xacro which loads cleanly in the
  MoveIt2 Setup Assistant. Key differences from the original:
    - Uses <robot> as root (not <root>) so the URDF parser finds the
      robot element immediately without xacro pre-processing.
    - kinova.gazebo is NOT included here — Gazebo plugins are simulation-only
      and cause the Setup Assistant to crash on load.
    - All joint/link properties are inlined — no dependency on macro files
      that pull in Gazebo content transitively.
    - package:// mesh URIs are kept (Setup Assistant resolves them if
      kinova_description is on ROS_PACKAGE_PATH, which it is after sourcing
      the workspace).

  Usage:
    source ~/Downloads/rl_v2-master-master/install/setup.bash
    export QT_QPA_PLATFORM=xcb
    ros2 launch moveit_setup_assistant setup_assistant.launch.py \
      robot_description:="$(xacro /path/to/j2n6s300_standalone.xacro)"
-->
